goals.question: What is the distribution of cloud cover in Seattle throughout the year?

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('seattle-weather-hourly-normals.csv')

# Convert date fields to date types
data['date_time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date_time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date_time'])]

# Extract month from date_time
data['month'] = data['date_time'].dt.month

# Compute average temperature by month
avg_temp_by_month = data.groupby('month')['temperature'].mean().reset_index()

# Plot line chart of average temperature by month
sns.lineplot(x='month', y='temperature', data=avg_temp_by_month, color='blue')

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the average temperature distribution in Seattle throughout the year?', wrap=True)

# Set x-axis label
plt.xlabel('Month')

# Set y-axis label
plt.ylabel('Average Temperature')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('seattle-weather-hourly-normals.csv')

# Convert date fields to date types
data['date_time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date_time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date_time'])]

# Extract month from date_time
data['month'] = data['date_time'].dt.month
```

```
# Group data by month and calculate average wind speed
avg_wind_speed = data.groupby('month')['wind_speed'].mean().reset_index()

# Create line chart
sns.lineplot(x='month', y='wind_speed', data=avg_wind_speed)

# Set chart title and axis labels
plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed in Seattle throughout the year?')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Average Wind Speed')

# Add horizontal line for average wind speed
avg_wind_speed_mean = avg_wind_speed['wind_speed'].mean()
plt.axhline(y=avg_wind_speed_mean, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Wind Speed: {avg_wind_speed_mean:.2f}')

# Add legend
plt.legend()

# Show chart
plt.show()
```
